</paragraph>
<paragraph id="156F570EFFBAFFC4B1AD55CDFD29FC06" blockId="53.[151,1437,151,1221]" box="[199,645,942,969]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B1AD55CDFE27FC07" bold="true" box="[199,395,942,969]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Natural enemies</emphasis>
: Not recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="6DC7179EFFBAFFC4B33A55CDFD2DFC06" box="[592,641,943,969]" name="Iran" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5DCA0485FFBAFFC4B1AD55B0FDBDFB0A" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="156F570EFFBAFFC4B1AD55B0FB9BFBB2" blockId="53.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B1AD55B0FEE4FC23" bold="true" box="[199,328,978,1004]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Comments</emphasis>
: The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFBAFFC4B3EC55B1FB5BFC22" authority="Moghaddam (Moghaddam 2013 a)" authorityName="Moghaddam (Moghaddam" authorityYear="2013" box="[646,1271,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Peliococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilamicus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B3EC55B1FCDEFC22" box="[646,882,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Peliococcus ilamicus</emphasis>
Moghaddam (
<bibRefCitation id="71412AFFFFBAFFC4B57E55B1FB43FC22" author="Moghaddam, M." box="[1044,1263,979,1005]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref94836" refString="Moghaddam, M. (2013 a) A review of the mealybugs (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Pseudococcidae, Putoidae and Rhizoecidae) of Iran, with descriptions of four new species and three new records for the Iranian fauna. Zootaxa, 3632 (1), 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3632.1.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Moghaddam 2013a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to the morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFBAFFC4B0E65595FD81FBDE" box="[396,557,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Erimococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kimmericus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B0E65595FD81FBDE" box="[396,557,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">E. kimmericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the small differences in the distribution of the dorsal clusters of tubular ducts between 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFBAFFC4B1945279FED6FBFA" authorityName="Moghaddam (Moghaddam" authorityYear="2013" box="[254,378,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Peliococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilamicus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B1945279FED6FBFA" box="[254,378,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">P. ilamicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFBAFFC4B0DF5279FDF4FBFA" box="[437,600,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Erimococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kimmericus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B0DF5279FDF4FBFA" box="[437,600,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">E. kimmericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are considered to represent geographic and intraspecific variability in 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFBAFFC4B4EE5279FEB4FB96" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Erimococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kimmericus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B4EE5279FEB4FB96" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">E. kimmericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a widely distributed and highly polymorphic species, so 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFBAFFC4B2D6525DFB96FB96" authorityName="Moghaddam (Moghaddam" authorityYear="2013" box="[956,1082,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Peliococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilamicus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B2D6525DFB96FB96" box="[956,1082,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">P. ilamicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered to be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="D2D02C8DFFBAFFC4B0495201FD77FBB1" authority="(Kiritshenko)" baseAuthorityName="Kiritshenko" box="[291,731,1123,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Erimococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kimmericus">
<emphasis id="27A48B1CFFBAFFC4B0495201FD91FBB2" box="[291,573,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Erimococcus kimmericus</emphasis>
(Kiritshenko)
</taxonomicName>
by Danzig &amp; Gavrilov (2014).
</paragraph>
